General to all SDGs

Introduction

The United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs) challenge the global community to build a world where no one is left behind.

Since 2018, Elsevier has generated SDG search queries to help researchers and institutions track and demonstrate progress toward the SDG targets. In the past 3 years, these queries, along with the universitys own data and evidence supporting progress and contributions to the particular SDG outside of research-based metrics, are used for the THE Impact Rankings.

Method

For 2022, this SDG uses the exact same search query and ML algorithm as the Elsevier 2021 SDG mapping. Full details of the 2021 methodology are available on Digital Commons Data.

SDG 7 - Ensure access to affordable, reliable, sustainable and modern energy for all

Explore this wordcloud plus the most active contributors on the SciVal SDG site

Journals

In this section, we show how the publication set, captured by the query above, relates to scholarly journals. Journals are sorted in terms of their relevance using term frequency-inverse document frequency (TF-IDF). The horizontal bars are proportional to the number of publications contributed by the journal to the current publication set. The number alongside the horizontal bar is the proportion of the journal contributing to this publication set.

The articles on this topic are published most frequently in the following journals: International Journal of Hydrogen Energy (30,698 publications), Journal of Power Sources (22,323), and Energies (16,299).

Note, larger journals may not appear in the table below, as their SDG contribution may be relatively small compared to the size of the journal.

Keywords

Elseviers Scopus database of scientific literature, was used for the table below. The document types included in the data sets are journal articles, reviews, short surveys and conference papers, covering the period 19962022. We refer to these documents collectively as publications or papers.

In order to help better illustrate the content of this set of publications, indicators associated with the keywords most specific to this set (according to a TF-IDF score) are presented below.
